excesses of between 7% and 41%. A minimum mortality rate of 224 per 100,000 was 
estimated to result from elimination of one risk factor for each of the nine 
diseases, indicating state excesses from 26% to 54%, or 524,000 US deaths. 
Reduction of US mortality from the nine diseases to the risk factor--eliminated 
rate is estimated to be associated with an increased life expectancy at birth of 
4 years.

